Uses of Package
com.st.st25sdk.type5

  • Packages that use com.st.st25sdk.type5 
    Package Description
    com.st.st25sdk.command
    Defines methods to build the commands for: Iso7816, Iso14443, Iso15693, NFC Forum type 4, NFC Forum type 5, Vicinity including high level commands for NDEF messages
    com.st.st25sdk.type5
    Provides classes to handle NFC Forum Type5 Family Tags and Dynamic Tags.
    com.st.st25sdk.type5.lri
    Defines all Tags classes to handle LRi series The LRIS64K is a contactless memory powered by the received carrier electromagnetic wave, which follows the ISO/IEC 15693 and ISO/IEC 18000-3 mode 1 recommendation for radio-frequency power and signal interface.
    com.st.st25sdk.type5.m24lr
    Defines all Tags classes to handle M24LR series The M24LR series devices are Dynamic NFC/RFID tags IC with a dual-interface, electrically erasable programmable memory (EEPROM).
    com.st.st25sdk.type5.st25dv
    Provide API related to ST25DV Family Tags and Dynamic Tags including following main features according to product: Password management Area configuration Configurations with access to Static/Dynamic registers Fast Transfer Mode Extended commands
    com.st.st25sdk.type5.st25dvpwm  
    com.st.st25sdk.type5.st25tv
    Provides classes to handle ST25TV Tags (NFC Forum Type5) from STMicroelectronics.
